1
00:00:43,211 --> 00:00:45,338
[ Narrator ]
The future:

2
00:00:45,413 --> 00:00:47,813
The polar ice caps
have melted,

3
00:00:47,882 --> 00:00:50,612
covering the Earth
with water.

4
00:00:50,685 --> 00:00:55,088
Those who survived
have adapted...

5
00:00:55,156 --> 00:00:57,090
to a new world.

6
00:02:26,013 --> 00:02:28,743
[ Gargling ]

7
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:39,592
[ Metal Clangs ]

8
00:05:08,209 --> 00:05:10,143
[ Whistles ]

9
00:05:26,027 --> 00:05:29,360
Bad luck, English.

10
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:33,992
But the Slavers are producing
a good grade of poxy these days.

11
00:05:34,068 --> 00:05:36,935
Cost you a handful of dirt--
or maybe that wind chime.

12
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:40,770
- What are you doin' here ?
- Just waiting.

13
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:43,867
Take your hand
off the sail.

14
00:05:43,944 --> 00:05:46,412
Take it off !

15
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:50,348
l've seen your boat before.
Haven't seen you.

16
00:05:51,419 --> 00:05:54,149
Took it legal.

17
00:05:54,221 --> 00:05:57,122
Previous owner was dead on the tiller
when l found it.

18
00:05:57,191 --> 00:06:00,126
You had another hour
before l traded up again.

19
00:06:00,194 --> 00:06:02,788
[ Laughing ]
Just improving my means.

20
00:06:04,298 --> 00:06:06,630
- Well, l owe you then.
- No, thanks.

21
00:06:06,701 --> 00:06:11,900
l got all the supplies l need.
Just came from an atoll.

22
00:06:11,972 --> 00:06:14,964
Eight days east,
if you're interested.

23
00:06:17,144 --> 00:06:20,807
- Two drifters meet,
something needs to be exchanged.
- l know the code.

24
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:23,509
But l'll give you this one
for free.

25
00:06:25,086 --> 00:06:27,020
Nothing's free
in Waterworld.

26
00:06:27,088 --> 00:06:28,556
Ha-ha. Yeah.

27
00:06:28,556 --> 00:06:29,488
Ha-ha. Yeah.

28
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,264
Smokers.

29
00:06:42,336 --> 00:06:44,361
Just enough wind
to get away clean.

30
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:50,266
[ Drifter ]
Forget the bag.

31
00:06:54,281 --> 00:06:58,149
lt's not worth it. You'll never
make it with your sails down.

32
00:06:58,219 --> 00:07:00,710
Hey !
[ Laughing ]

33
00:07:00,788 --> 00:07:02,756
[ Gobbling Sound,
Laughing ]

34
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,795
What can l say ?
[ Laughing ]

35
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:38,288
- Joe, he's goin' for it.
- What the hell ?

36
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:45,389
Never seen that before.

37
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:51,468
Here we go ! Go !
Drive ! Drive !

38
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:59,579
Faster ! Faster ! Whoo !

39
00:08:20,434 --> 00:08:22,698
Come on ! He's gonna get it !
He's gonna get it !

40
00:08:42,389 --> 00:08:44,653
- Pick her up !
- Get it ! Get it !

41
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:46,716
[ lndistinct Shout ]

42
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,146
[ Curses ln Hindi ]

43
00:09:13,587 --> 00:09:16,181
Oh, no !

44
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:26,555
[ Shouting, Gunfire ]

45
00:09:27,635 --> 00:09:31,127
[ Screaming ]

46
00:10:02,432 --> 00:10:05,333
lnbound !
Straight out from the gates.

47
00:10:14,811 --> 00:10:16,745
English.

48
00:10:19,415 --> 00:10:23,476
Flag's down, drifter.
We got enough traders.

49
00:10:29,625 --> 00:10:32,594
[ Murmuring ]

50
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:39,795
Dirt.

51
00:10:39,869 --> 00:10:41,803
Open the gates !

52
00:11:20,977 --> 00:11:23,639
[ Man Coughing,
People Chattering ]

53
00:11:23,713 --> 00:11:26,546
[ Man ]
Bones to berries.

54
00:11:26,616 --> 00:11:28,709
Veins to vine.

55
00:11:28,785 --> 00:11:32,983
These tendons to trees.
This blood to brine.

56
00:11:33,055 --> 00:11:34,716
Too old she was.

57
00:11:34,791 --> 00:11:39,353
This woman does leave us,
recycled and enshrined...

58
00:11:39,428 --> 00:11:42,295
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

59
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:54,139
[ Boys Chattering ]

60
00:12:00,383 --> 00:12:04,877
- [ Boys Complaining ]
- What is that ?

61
00:12:09,392 --> 00:12:11,792
You know me ?

62
00:12:11,861 --> 00:12:13,795
l know what you are.

63
00:12:13,863 --> 00:12:17,663
Good. Then you know if you
look for trouble while you're here,

64
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:19,792
you'll find more
than you can handle.

65
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:23,664
You got two hours.

66
00:12:26,275 --> 00:12:28,209
l'll only need one.

67
00:12:38,354 --> 00:12:40,879
[ Boy ]
He's comin' over here.

68
00:12:46,329 --> 00:12:48,263
- Me.
- You each get one...

69
00:12:48,331 --> 00:12:50,856
if everything's here
when l get back.

70
00:12:59,675 --> 00:13:01,540
- Pure dirt.
- [ People Murmuring ]

71
00:13:01,611 --> 00:13:04,011
3.2 kilos.

72
00:13:06,015 --> 00:13:09,212
How'd you come by
so much of it ?

73
00:13:09,285 --> 00:13:12,049
Another atoll
30 horizons west of here.

74
00:13:12,121 --> 00:13:14,248
Where'd they get it ?

75
00:13:14,323 --> 00:13:17,554
- They didn't say.
- [ Man ] We heard about that place--

76
00:13:17,627 --> 00:13:20,187
that they was all killed.

77
00:13:21,964 --> 00:13:24,194
- That's why they didn't say.
- Smokers ?

78
00:13:24,267 --> 00:13:27,464
Maybe Smokers,
maybe Slavers.

79
00:13:28,905 --> 00:13:31,738
So what's the word ?
We tradin' or not ?

80
00:13:31,807 --> 00:13:36,540
We'll tally it
like, uh, pure hydro.

81
00:13:40,116 --> 00:13:43,085
Works out to... 62 chits.

82
00:13:43,152 --> 00:13:45,950
[ Coins Clanging ]

83
00:13:46,022 --> 00:13:47,956
l want twice that.

84
00:13:48,024 --> 00:13:51,687
[ Onlookers Murmuring ]

85
00:13:51,761 --> 00:13:55,822
- l just want one sip of hydro !
- No, not 'til you tell me.

86
00:13:55,898 --> 00:13:59,129
She got inkings on her back.
l seen her.

87
00:13:59,201 --> 00:14:02,398
They say if you read
the marks on the child,

88
00:14:02,471 --> 00:14:05,929
they'll lead ya
all the way to Dryland.

89
00:14:06,008 --> 00:14:09,102
- Dryland's a myth.
- Some still believe.

90
00:14:09,178 --> 00:14:12,272
They say the Smokers
even got an eye out for her.

91
00:14:13,983 --> 00:14:17,043
Well, then, we'd better
keep it to ourselves.

92
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:43,645
- Help you ?
- Yeah.

93
00:14:43,713 --> 00:14:45,977
- Where's the store ?
- You found it.

94
00:14:51,754 --> 00:14:53,688
You don't have much.

95
00:14:54,924 --> 00:14:57,552
You the man
with the dirt ?

96
00:15:15,077 --> 00:15:16,635
Skoal.

97
00:15:20,282 --> 00:15:22,842
- One more.
- Make it two.

98
00:15:22,918 --> 00:15:26,684
A man this rich will buy
for a fellow outwater, l'm sure.

99
00:15:26,756 --> 00:15:29,088
One.

100
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:35,394
That's an interesting
pair of boots you got.

101
00:15:35,464 --> 00:15:37,625
- Trade ?
- No.

102
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,793
Shame.

103
00:15:46,509 --> 00:15:49,478
Enola.
Hey, what are you doing ?

104
00:15:49,545 --> 00:15:53,345
- No, you can't do that.
- l need another piece.
l want to draw some more.

105
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:56,044
l'll get it to you.
Just stay in the back.

106
00:15:56,118 --> 00:15:59,246
With all those chits,
you could order up a bath.

107
00:15:59,321 --> 00:16:01,949
- Have you ever had a freshwater bath ?
- Why are you talkin' to me ?

108
00:16:02,024 --> 00:16:03,958
Just being friendly.

109
00:16:09,231 --> 00:16:11,563
- ls that a tomato plant ?
- Yeah.

110
00:16:11,634 --> 00:16:13,829
You have a keen eye.

111
00:16:13,903 --> 00:16:15,962
Saw one in a picture.
How much ?

112
00:16:22,211 --> 00:16:24,145
Half your chits.

113
00:16:35,691 --> 00:16:38,785
- l'll take them too.
- Take what ?

114
00:16:38,861 --> 00:16:41,887
- You bought everything.
- l'll take them shelves.

115
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,858
So, what did you see out there
in your 15 months ?

116
00:16:47,937 --> 00:16:50,428
- Such as ?
- An end to all this water.

117
00:16:50,506 --> 00:16:54,033
Askin' the wrong person.

118
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:56,101
- The one they buried today ?
- Uh-huh ?

119
00:16:56,178 --> 00:16:58,703
She found the only end there is.

120
00:17:03,886 --> 00:17:05,820
l've got a proposition
for you, Mariner.

121
00:17:07,723 --> 00:17:12,683
- l'm not staying.
- We're not asking you to.
All we want is your seed.

122
00:17:13,996 --> 00:17:16,931
We can look to our own
for impregnation,

123
00:17:16,999 --> 00:17:22,369
but too much of that sort of thing
gets... undesirable.

124
00:17:22,438 --> 00:17:25,430
When she's pregnant,
you go on your way...

125
00:17:25,508 --> 00:17:28,102
with all the supplies
you need.

126
00:17:28,177 --> 00:17:32,170
You don't have anything.
You're dying.

127
00:17:36,852 --> 00:17:40,583
No man stays out that long
and turns down a woman.

128
00:17:41,924 --> 00:17:46,156
- He's hiding something.
- Maybe he's a Smoker spy.

129
00:17:48,764 --> 00:17:50,823
[ Whistles ]

130
00:17:56,634 --> 00:17:59,797
When the elders say so,
you can leave,

131
00:17:59,871 --> 00:18:01,805
and not before.

132
00:18:20,958 --> 00:18:22,892
Gills.

133
00:18:23,961 --> 00:18:27,988
- Mutation !
- He's a mutant !

134
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:30,829
[ Screaming ]
My hand !

135
00:18:34,639 --> 00:18:38,336
[ Screaming ]

136
00:18:38,409 --> 00:18:41,901
[ Man Shouting,
lndistinct ]

137
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,449
Throw the nets !

138
00:19:01,499 --> 00:19:05,492
[ Crowd Yelling ]

139
00:19:18,015 --> 00:19:19,949
[ Screams ]

140
00:19:20,017 --> 00:19:22,918
By what right--

141
00:19:24,355 --> 00:19:27,222
You pay me to keep the peace.

142
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,225
This isn't it.

143
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:32,729
- He has killed one of ours.
- He was defending himself.

144
00:19:32,797 --> 00:19:36,528
- He needs to be destroyed !
- Kill him. Let's kill him.
- That may be,

145
00:19:36,601 --> 00:19:39,900
but not here
and not like this.

146
00:20:12,003 --> 00:20:13,868
[ Boy ]
What is it ?

147
00:20:13,938 --> 00:20:15,906
Damn.

148
00:20:17,108 --> 00:20:20,305
lt's tied.
l can't get it off.

149
00:20:23,814 --> 00:20:27,079
Open the gate.

150
00:20:29,787 --> 00:20:32,051
[ Laughing ]

151
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:42,825
 [ Humming ]

152
00:20:58,349 --> 00:21:01,716
ls it a map ?

153
00:21:01,786 --> 00:21:05,449
- You'd tell me if you knew,
wouldn't you, Enola ?
- Mm-hmm.

154
00:21:08,926 --> 00:21:11,827
- What are you drawing ?
- l don't know.

155
00:21:13,264 --> 00:21:17,701
Helen, look. Look at
the prodigal child's latest vision.

156
00:21:20,404 --> 00:21:23,339
[ Chuckling ]

157
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:28,504
- How soon before we can leave ?
- l don't have any idea yet
where we can go.

158
00:21:28,579 --> 00:21:31,912
l haven't figured out
the tattoo on her back.

159
00:21:31,983 --> 00:21:35,612
l'm a stupid man.
The answer's right there.

160
00:21:35,686 --> 00:21:37,677
lt's just beyond me.

161
00:21:40,725 --> 00:21:42,818
Maybe he knows.

162
00:21:51,502 --> 00:21:55,996
Oh, yes, l see.
They are webbed.

163
00:21:56,073 --> 00:21:59,839
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, nine,
ten digits. That's wonderful.

164
00:21:59,910 --> 00:22:02,902
They tell me, too,
that you have gills.

165
00:22:02,980 --> 00:22:07,610
lsotropic gills. Are they merely
vestigial or are they functional now ?

166
00:22:07,685 --> 00:22:11,212
My name is Gregor. l've just come
to pay you a little vi-- vi--

167
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:16,055
Oh, my God.
[ Laughing ]

168
00:22:16,127 --> 00:22:19,187
l'm sorry.
l'm not laughing at you.

169
00:22:19,263 --> 00:22:22,323
l'm excited. Your gills.
They're functional.

170
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:26,029
lcthyus sapien.
You can breathe in the water.

171
00:22:26,103 --> 00:22:29,971
How deep can you go ?
Look, l'm only here...

172
00:22:30,041 --> 00:22:32,635
because l want to learn
more about you.

173
00:22:32,710 --> 00:22:34,644
[ Spitting ]

174
00:22:37,748 --> 00:22:41,115
You don't like humans
very much, do you ?

175
00:22:41,185 --> 00:22:44,780
l can't say that l blame you.
But tell me:

176
00:22:44,855 --> 00:22:48,450
- Are all of your kind as
bad-tempered as you are ?
- [ Slamming Cage ]

177
00:22:51,062 --> 00:22:53,530
- l have no ''kind.''
- Oh, fish rot.

178
00:22:53,597 --> 00:22:56,998
l'd be surprised if there
weren't others, and if there aren't,

179
00:22:57,068 --> 00:23:00,469
there will be eventually.

180
00:23:00,538 --> 00:23:03,871
Anyway, l've come here
because l need to ask you a question.

181
00:23:03,941 --> 00:23:07,877
Where-- Where did
your dirt come from ?

182
00:23:07,945 --> 00:23:10,345
ls it from Dryland ?

183
00:23:10,414 --> 00:23:12,541
Do you know what this is ?

184
00:23:14,485 --> 00:23:16,885
The ancients-- They did something
terrible, didn't they ?

185
00:23:16,954 --> 00:23:20,720
To cause all this water.
Hundreds-- Hundreds of years ago.

186
00:23:20,791 --> 00:23:23,817
lf l tell you,
will you open this lock ?

187
00:23:26,330 --> 00:23:29,197
l haven't a key.

188
00:23:29,266 --> 00:23:31,996
- There's a mooring cleat down there.
- What ?

189
00:23:32,069 --> 00:23:35,129
- Good as any key.
- A mooring cleat ?

190
00:23:37,208 --> 00:23:39,972
l won't hurt anyone.
l'll just leave.

191
00:23:41,312 --> 00:23:44,611
- l'll be right back.
- [ Man ] Gregor !

192
00:23:44,682 --> 00:23:46,650
What's your business there ?

193
00:23:46,717 --> 00:23:48,844
- Move along !
- l'm not a brave man.

194
00:23:48,919 --> 00:23:53,219
lf you know anything about Dryland,
please tell me. Please !

195
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:56,492
Don't let it die with you.

196
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:59,290
No, no, no, no.
Stop !

197
00:23:59,363 --> 00:24:03,026
[ Man ]
Gregor ! Move along !

198
00:24:37,902 --> 00:24:43,101
[ Elder ]
After considerable deliberation
of the evidence at hand,

199
00:24:43,174 --> 00:24:46,632
it is our decision
that this mute-o...

200
00:24:46,710 --> 00:24:49,941
does, indeed,
constitute a threat.

201
00:24:50,014 --> 00:24:52,983
Therefore, in the interest
of public safety,

202
00:24:53,050 --> 00:24:56,577
he is hereby sentenced
to be recycled...

203
00:24:56,654 --> 00:24:59,521
in the customary fashion.

204
00:24:59,590 --> 00:25:01,490
Proceed.

205
00:25:07,398 --> 00:25:10,231
l'm sorry.

206
00:25:14,038 --> 00:25:16,131
Bones to berries.

207
00:25:16,207 --> 00:25:18,801
Veins to vines.

208
00:25:18,876 --> 00:25:22,642
His tendons to trees.
His blood to brine.

209
00:25:22,713 --> 00:25:25,807
Too strange for life he was.

210
00:25:25,883 --> 00:25:30,343
This mute-o now does leave us,

211
00:25:30,421 --> 00:25:33,292
recycled and entombed,

212
00:25:33,425 --> 00:25:36,519
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

213
00:25:46,471 --> 00:25:51,204
Smokers !
Dead out of the sun !

214
00:25:54,379 --> 00:25:57,815
To your posts !

215
00:26:10,495 --> 00:26:12,463
[ Confused Shouting, Screaming ]

216
00:26:12,531 --> 00:26:15,432
[ Woman ]
Oh, my God ! Oh, my God !

217
00:26:25,777 --> 00:26:28,507
- Kill !
- There !

218
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:30,810
[ Screaming ]

219
00:26:34,853 --> 00:26:38,482
[ lndistinct Shouting ]

220
00:26:38,557 --> 00:26:41,390
We are safe
behind these walls.

221
00:26:42,894 --> 00:26:44,828
- Aren't we ?
- [ lndistinct Shout ]

222
00:26:50,669 --> 00:26:53,763
- [ lndistinct Shout ]
- Let me out !

223
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,772
Let me out !
l'll fight !

224
00:27:06,018 --> 00:27:07,952
[ Shouting Commands ]

225
00:27:27,205 --> 00:27:29,139
Give me the key
to the city now.

226
00:27:32,978 --> 00:27:35,310
Let's go !
Let's go ! Let's go !

227
00:27:37,983 --> 00:27:40,884
Floor it !
Floor it ! Floor it !

228
00:27:56,868 --> 00:27:59,428
[ Woman Screaming ]

229
00:28:02,107 --> 00:28:04,473
Swab it ! Swab it !

230
00:28:04,543 --> 00:28:08,206
Goddamn ! More ammo !

231
00:28:22,594 --> 00:28:24,653
[ Smoker ]
Break down the door !

232
00:28:24,730 --> 00:28:26,721
[ Screaming ]

233
00:28:28,433 --> 00:28:31,527
- My God !
- [ Screaming ]

234
00:28:31,603 --> 00:28:34,003
[ Woman Thrusting Spear ]
Ha !

235
00:28:34,072 --> 00:28:36,131
[ Screaming ]

236
00:28:36,208 --> 00:28:39,200
We'll have this atoll
in no time.

237
00:28:42,481 --> 00:28:44,449
Crank it !
Crank it !

238
00:28:48,487 --> 00:28:50,751
Look !

239
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:04,230
[ Men Shouting ]

240
00:29:09,441 --> 00:29:11,636
Look out !

241
00:29:19,451 --> 00:29:22,420
[ Gunfire, Shouting ]

242
00:29:34,166 --> 00:29:36,100
Oh, no !

243
00:29:47,012 --> 00:29:49,810
You get that goin' !
Fill 'em up !

244
00:29:56,521 --> 00:29:59,319
[ Smoker Yelling,
Atoll People Screaming ]

245
00:30:01,026 --> 00:30:03,051
[ Screaming ]

246
00:30:27,752 --> 00:30:31,119
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Gregor ] Helen, come quickly !

247
00:30:31,189 --> 00:30:33,350
Helen !

248
00:30:42,701 --> 00:30:45,670
[ Man Screaming, Gunfire ]

249
00:31:01,353 --> 00:31:04,789
You're not supposed to go yet !

250
00:31:04,856 --> 00:31:07,222
