346
00:41:44,552 --> 00:41:46,486
You and l are.

347
00:41:48,056 --> 00:41:51,184
The kid we gotta pitch
over the side.

348
00:41:53,027 --> 00:41:57,054
- What ?
- My boat's tore up.

349
00:41:57,131 --> 00:41:59,622
l'm takin' on water.

350
00:41:59,701 --> 00:42:03,137
l'd be lucky to get
half a hydro ration out of that.

351
00:42:03,204 --> 00:42:06,833
You know--
l said l won't drink.

352
00:42:06,908 --> 00:42:09,468
For 12 days ?

353
00:42:11,045 --> 00:42:13,980
No. lt's better
one of you dies now...

354
00:42:14,048 --> 00:42:16,107
than both of you die slow.

355
00:42:16,184 --> 00:42:18,379
Wait. Wait.

356
00:42:18,453 --> 00:42:20,921
We saved your life.
We got you out.

357
00:42:20,989 --> 00:42:25,085
No, you got me out so you
could get out. We're even.

358
00:42:25,159 --> 00:42:27,184
She can cook.
She can fish.

359
00:42:27,261 --> 00:42:29,525
- So can l.
- Then take my necklace.
Take my necklace.

360
00:42:29,597 --> 00:42:31,861
- l got better ones below.
- No, look !

361
00:42:31,933 --> 00:42:34,766
Oh.

362
00:42:34,836 --> 00:42:37,930
After what you went through
back there on the atoll,

363
00:42:38,006 --> 00:42:41,169
l can understand
why you would want to.

364
00:42:41,242 --> 00:42:43,233
But she's a child.

365
00:42:43,311 --> 00:42:46,906
 [ Enola Humming ]

366
00:42:54,288 --> 00:42:56,688
ls there something else then ?

367
00:43:02,096 --> 00:43:04,690
Enola ! Go below.

368
00:43:05,833 --> 00:43:07,767
Enola.

369
00:43:18,146 --> 00:43:21,445
Yeah. You said so yourself.

370
00:43:23,351 --> 00:43:26,081
Been out there a long time.

371
00:44:11,766 --> 00:44:14,792
Couple hours ago,
l was potential dirt to you.

372
00:44:14,869 --> 00:44:18,270
- We're not like that.
- You all are.

373
00:44:23,845 --> 00:44:27,144
Know what l was really thinkin' ?

374
00:44:27,215 --> 00:44:30,378
Why l don't drop both of you
in my wake right now.

375
00:44:31,686 --> 00:44:34,246
You got nothin' l need.

376
00:44:50,171 --> 00:44:52,537
You're taking us to Dryland.

377
00:44:56,911 --> 00:44:59,709
Killing's a hard thing to do well.

378
00:44:59,781 --> 00:45:03,217
- Believe me. l'm not
the one to start on.
- Both of us !

379
00:45:08,723 --> 00:45:11,317
How long you plan
to hold that on me ?

380
00:45:11,392 --> 00:45:13,553
As long as it takes.

381
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:19,156
- Okay.
- No !

382
00:45:20,835 --> 00:45:23,963
Let me out of here !

383
00:45:24,038 --> 00:45:27,872
Where the hell are you ?
Don't you touch my child.

384
00:45:27,942 --> 00:45:29,876
Come here !
[ lndistinct Shouting ]

385
00:45:31,179 --> 00:45:33,409
[ Groaning ]

386
00:46:18,092 --> 00:46:20,822
Okay, now don't move, okay ?
There.

387
00:46:20,895 --> 00:46:24,296
Ohh. Oh, lookin'
real good, yeah.

388
00:46:24,365 --> 00:46:26,697
There. There.

389
00:46:26,767 --> 00:46:28,701
All done.

390
00:46:28,769 --> 00:46:31,761
Now, there may be some small problem
in depth perception.

391
00:46:31,839 --> 00:46:34,706
Well, it better not
screw up my short game.

392
00:46:37,144 --> 00:46:39,578
- Well ?
- [ Smokers ] Looks good.
l like it. Yeah.

393
00:46:39,647 --> 00:46:42,741
- l like it better than your real eye.
- Much better.

394
00:46:42,817 --> 00:46:46,344
- What do you say, Toby ? The truth.
- Looks like shit.

395
00:46:46,420 --> 00:46:49,321
That's why l love children.
No guile.

396
00:46:53,628 --> 00:46:57,086
lt does look like shit.

397
00:46:57,164 --> 00:46:59,098
And it feels like cold shit !

398
00:46:59,166 --> 00:47:01,657
Deacon ? What--

399
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:06,164
l'm sorry. l-lt's just that
there's a problem in the pit.

400
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:08,174
Maybe you should come.

401
00:47:13,714 --> 00:47:17,047
- Let's drive.
- [ Chattering ]

402
00:47:22,690 --> 00:47:26,353
The pit. Don't bother
with the scenic route.

403
00:47:26,427 --> 00:47:28,361
[ Deacon ] Drive !

404
00:47:29,497 --> 00:47:31,692
Hey, it's drivin' better.

405
00:47:43,678 --> 00:47:45,942
Get off !

406
00:47:47,014 --> 00:47:49,414
Get over there.
Get out of the way.

407
00:47:49,483 --> 00:47:51,610
All right, all right, all right.
Okay, okay.

408
00:47:54,855 --> 00:47:58,291
You guys are great.
Bless all you cousins over there.

409
00:47:58,359 --> 00:48:02,851
Keep up the good work.
Growth is progress. Growth is progress.

410
00:48:02,984 --> 00:48:07,512
Somebody !
Hey, up there !

411
00:48:07,589 --> 00:48:09,523
Take it off !

412
00:48:11,993 --> 00:48:15,326
- Yes.
- Your Deaconship.

413
00:48:15,396 --> 00:48:19,332
Hello. Good morning.
Or night,

414
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:21,925
whichever the case may be.

415
00:48:22,003 --> 00:48:24,870
- What is it ? l'm a busy man.
- l thought you should know.

416
00:48:24,939 --> 00:48:27,601
We're down to exactly...

417
00:48:27,675 --> 00:48:31,668
four feet, nine inches
