Oh, l know.

499
00:57:37,525 --> 00:57:40,255
But you ran away.
l-- What ?

500
00:57:40,327 --> 00:57:44,161
What are you do--
No ! Please, no ! No !

501
00:57:48,936 --> 00:57:51,029
[ Grunting ]

502
00:57:53,240 --> 00:57:57,540
Don't ever touch
anything on my boat again.

503
00:58:00,948 --> 00:58:02,939
She said she was sorry !

504
00:58:06,954 --> 00:58:09,752
That means you're supposed
to say something back !

505
00:58:33,013 --> 00:58:34,981
- Did you say somethin' ?
- [ Enola ] Mm-mmm.

506
00:58:59,091 --> 00:59:01,218
[ Deacon ] The child--
did he have the girl with him ?

507
00:59:01,293 --> 00:59:03,591
- [ Pilot ] Uh-huh.
- Seems to me if we launch now,

508
00:59:03,662 --> 00:59:05,789
we can cut him down
just about here.

509
00:59:07,633 --> 00:59:11,000
- lf he doesn't change course.
- Ah, it's not likely.

510
00:59:11,069 --> 00:59:14,698
He's a wily one,
that ichthy-demon.

511
00:59:14,773 --> 00:59:17,367
Yeah, if he knows
he's been spotted,

512
00:59:17,443 --> 00:59:21,243
he'll expect us to expect him
to change course,

513
00:59:21,313 --> 00:59:24,874
which is exactly why
he'll keep his heading.

514
00:59:24,950 --> 00:59:28,181
The important question is,
where's he heading ?

515
00:59:28,253 --> 00:59:31,814
And does he know
how precious his cargo is ?

516
00:59:31,890 --> 00:59:36,259
l say that he's headed here,
and we take him here.

517
00:59:43,836 --> 00:59:47,101
[ Drifter Shouting ]

518
00:59:47,172 --> 00:59:49,367
- Drifter ?
- Mm-hmm.

519
00:59:49,441 --> 00:59:51,375
- [ Shouting Continues ]
- [ Helen ] Are we gonna stop ?

520
00:59:51,443 --> 00:59:53,377
- Look at the flag !
- His flag's up.

521
00:59:53,445 --> 00:59:55,538
l thought you all
stopped for each other.

522
01:00:00,853 --> 01:00:03,515
Well... maybe he has some food !

523
01:00:07,025 --> 01:00:09,619
Don't find many who follow
the rules anymore.

524
01:00:09,695 --> 01:00:12,528
Well, make it quick.
What's your business ?

525
01:00:17,503 --> 01:00:19,471
Trade.

526
01:00:21,406 --> 01:00:23,397
You got any resin ?

527
01:00:25,944 --> 01:00:30,074
Resin ? He's gotta be out of
his mind. He's out of his mind.
l don't have any resin.

528
01:00:30,148 --> 01:00:32,616
- [ Babbling ]
- You been outwater
a long time, haven't you ?

529
01:00:34,453 --> 01:00:36,887
Must be jokin' me, man.
Resin ! You don't got enough.

530
01:00:36,955 --> 01:00:39,150
How 'bout food ?

531
01:00:39,224 --> 01:00:41,249
Could you say that again, please ?

532
01:00:41,326 --> 01:00:44,261
- How 'bout food ?
- Ah, yeah, food.

533
01:00:44,329 --> 01:00:46,820
Yeah, that'd be good, eh ?

534
01:00:46,899 --> 01:00:49,891
l haven't eaten in, well,
you know, forever.

535
01:00:51,136 --> 01:00:53,604
Which one of you two is a cook ?

536
01:00:53,672 --> 01:00:57,369
'Cause l usually fall for the waitress.
[ Chuckling ]

537
01:00:57,442 --> 01:00:59,433
Like you said,
l don't have much.

538
01:00:59,511 --> 01:01:02,742
Now listen, eh ? [ Mumbles ]
Let's see. What do l have to do ?

539
01:01:02,814 --> 01:01:06,648
We can start with that wee orchard
you got over there.

540
01:01:06,718 --> 01:01:11,587
- [ Whooping ]
- All right, hold it there.

541
01:01:11,657 --> 01:01:15,093
- [ Mariner ] We can talk.
- [ Drifter ] Fair enough.

542
01:01:15,160 --> 01:01:18,129
[ Babbling ]

543
01:01:20,065 --> 01:01:22,431
lt's a nice rod, isn't it ?

544
01:01:22,501 --> 01:01:25,527
l like that rod.
lt's a nice rod. [ Babbles ]

545
01:01:31,910 --> 01:01:34,674
Got yourself a wee harem
goin' here now, do ya ?

546
01:01:41,286 --> 01:01:43,379
What you want for the women ?

547
01:01:43,455 --> 01:01:45,855
We're not for sale.

548
01:01:45,924 --> 01:01:48,620
Not for sale ?
There's no such thing as not for sale.

549
01:01:48,694 --> 01:01:50,958
''Not for sale'' !
Not for sale, eh ?

550
01:01:52,965 --> 01:01:56,457
- Are they a pair or would you
consider sellin' 'em separate ?
- No.

551
01:01:56,535 --> 01:02:00,528
Our business is done here unless you got
some resin for sale you can part with.

552
01:02:00,606 --> 01:02:02,540
l told you once already,
l don't have it.

553
01:02:02,608 --> 01:02:05,372
l-l-l don't have it.
Don't have it. Don't have it.

554
01:02:05,444 --> 01:02:09,574
Haven't seen neither for trade
in lunars now. Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

555
01:02:12,784 --> 01:02:15,116
l do have somethin' that'll
make you change your mind.

556
01:02:16,388 --> 01:02:20,017
Somethin' that you can't pass on.
[ Giggles ]

557
01:02:20,092 --> 01:02:24,392
l took it off
an Atoller refugee camp.

558
01:02:24,463 --> 01:02:26,397
The life savings
of the entire clan.

559
01:02:34,373 --> 01:02:37,365
Paper.
[ Babbles ]

560
01:02:37,442 --> 01:02:42,937
lt's paper. Have you ever
seen paper ? Look at it.

561
01:02:43,015 --> 01:02:44,949
Smell it.

562
01:02:46,685 --> 01:02:48,778
l been savin' it
for a special trade.

563
01:02:51,923 --> 01:02:54,551
Don't you do it.

564
01:02:54,626 --> 01:02:57,527
You know, maybe l'm talkin'
to the wrong person here.

565
01:02:57,596 --> 01:02:59,757
Whose boat is this ?
ls it your boat or your boat ?

566
01:02:59,831 --> 01:03:03,460
No. No, it's his boat.
But he doesn't own us.

567
01:03:10,442 --> 01:03:12,467
Half an hour.

568
01:03:12,544 --> 01:03:16,105
[ Mumbling, Babbling ]
Out of his mind somethin' there.

569
01:03:16,181 --> 01:03:20,140
l got two pages in here, man !
l mean, l'd get half a dozen
girls with this, you know.

570
01:03:20,218 --> 01:03:22,880
Half an hour.

571
01:03:22,954 --> 01:03:25,081
- You tradin' or not ?
- Don't.

572
01:03:25,157 --> 01:03:27,125
Shut up.

573
01:03:28,694 --> 01:03:30,787
Okay.

574
01:03:32,397 --> 01:03:34,661
Forty-five minutes
with the wee one right there.

575
01:03:34,733 --> 01:03:37,167
l like to do the talkin',
if you know what l mean.

576
01:03:38,904 --> 01:03:40,838
No !

577
01:03:41,907 --> 01:03:44,967
Fair. Come, come,
come, come, come !

578
01:03:45,043 --> 01:03:47,409
No. My boat.

579
01:03:49,314 --> 01:03:52,750
- Fair enough. Fair enough.
Good, good, good. Aye.
- Helen.

580
01:03:52,818 --> 01:03:56,345
- Sit down.
- Enola, just do as he says.

581
01:03:58,590 --> 01:04:00,683
[ Chuckling ]

582
01:04:42,634 --> 01:04:45,626
lt's been a while for me now.

583
01:04:45,704 --> 01:04:49,299
Guess it's been
more than a while, actually.

584
01:04:52,477 --> 01:04:57,414
l've only got half an hour.
[ Repeating ] Half an hour,
half an hour, half an hour--

585
01:04:58,517 --> 01:05:00,451
[ Mumbles ]
Great, great, great--

586
01:05:00,519 --> 01:05:05,286
[ Gasps ] Ooh ! You're so beautiful.
Aye ! Anyone ever told you that ?

587
01:05:05,357 --> 01:05:08,292
Give me that. What are you doin' ?
lt's just a game.

588
01:05:11,696 --> 01:05:14,665
Oh, l, um-- l, uh--
We was just playin'.

589
01:05:17,803 --> 01:05:19,828
The trade's off.

590
01:05:19,905 --> 01:05:21,770
l changed my mind.

591
01:05:22,841 --> 01:05:25,833
Well, um-- Well,
you can't do that.

592
01:05:25,911 --> 01:05:28,379
l mean, a deal's a deal, eh ?

593
01:05:28,446 --> 01:05:30,277
l just did.

594
01:05:30,782 --> 01:05:32,579
Hey !

595
01:05:32,651 --> 01:05:37,179
She's mine. Aye. No. No, no
l own her. But-- No.

596
01:05:37,255 --> 01:05:40,156
- Go on.
- Get, get, get.
Go, go, go. Good, good.

597
01:05:40,225 --> 01:05:44,628
But don't go too far now.
This won't take but a minute.

598
01:05:49,734 --> 01:05:55,104
l hate this boat.
l hate this boat !

599
01:05:55,173 --> 01:05:57,869
You bastard.

600
01:06:02,080 --> 01:06:06,983
You-- You're pretty stingy for a man
who's got everything, aren't ya now ?

601
01:06:10,889 --> 01:06:13,084
Oh-h-h. Ohh.

602
01:06:20,098 --> 01:06:23,590
- [ Yells ]
- [ Crashing ]

603
01:06:23,668 --> 01:06:25,795
[ Drifter ]
Ah, you bastard !

604
01:06:25,871 --> 01:06:28,465
[ Banging, Crashing Continue ]

605
01:06:37,215 --> 01:06:39,240
Where's me boat ?

606
01:06:40,518 --> 01:06:42,645
Where's me boat ?

607
01:06:42,721 --> 01:06:46,782
[ Mumbling ]

608
01:06:49,961 --> 01:06:51,895
Help me to me boat.

609
01:06:53,431 --> 01:06:56,552
Ow ! Me boat.

610
01:06:57,553 --> 01:06:59,418
Me boat.

611
01:07:28,383 --> 01:07:30,317
[ Helen ]
What the-- No !

612
01:07:32,721 --> 01:07:35,019
Never catch anything
with this. lt's useless.

613
01:07:36,892 --> 01:07:38,826
[ Helen Gasps ]

614
01:07:40,863 --> 01:07:45,357
Look, l'm sorry.
You were right about the pole.

615
01:07:46,702 --> 01:07:49,170
You were right,
but we have to eat.

616
01:07:54,877 --> 01:07:56,868
Now l know
you can hear me !

617
01:07:56,945 --> 01:08:00,403
Now we can fish for ourselves.
You show us what to do.

618
01:08:00,482 --> 01:08:02,746
You must know how.
Even you gotta eat !

619
01:08:02,818 --> 01:08:05,184
You just sit there.

620
01:08:28,777 --> 01:08:31,746
- What--
- [ Mumbling ] l don't know.

621
01:09:07,582 --> 01:09:09,516
Happy now ?

622
01:09:13,789 --> 01:09:18,385
 [ Humming ]

623
01:09:18,460 --> 01:09:23,762
 [ Humming Continues ]

624
01:09:27,669 --> 01:09:29,603
You don't like my singing,
do you ?

625
01:09:32,541 --> 01:09:36,568
Helen says you don't like my singing
'cause you can't sing.

626
01:09:42,651 --> 01:09:45,347
- Ever try and listen ?
- To what ?

627
01:09:48,457 --> 01:09:50,687
The sound of the world.

628
01:09:54,863 --> 01:09:57,798
- l don't hear anything.
- That's because you're too loud,

629
01:09:57,866 --> 01:09:59,800
and you're movin' around
all the time.

630
01:09:59,868 --> 01:10:02,632
Try sittin' still.

631
01:10:02,704 --> 01:10:05,696
Eyeball ?

632
01:10:20,122 --> 01:10:22,147
l wish l had feet like his.

633
01:10:25,227 --> 01:10:27,127
Then maybe l could swim.

634
01:10:27,195 --> 01:10:28,856
Enola.

635
01:10:32,534 --> 01:10:34,627
[ Burps ] Sorry.

636
01:10:39,341 --> 01:10:41,809
Never met a person
couldn't swim before.

637
01:10:44,579 --> 01:10:47,412
l can't.

638
01:10:48,683 --> 01:10:50,981
People say l was weird.

639
01:10:51,053 --> 01:10:52,987
Maybe they were right.

640
01:10:56,525 --> 01:10:58,959
Maybe they were right
about you too.

641
01:11:26,788 --> 01:11:28,756
Enola wanted to give you this.

642
01:11:33,061 --> 01:11:35,689
And this.

643
01:11:37,833 --> 01:11:39,926
She won't take it again.

644
01:11:46,374 --> 01:11:49,309
You don't look much like her.

645
01:11:49,377 --> 01:11:53,404
- Well, l'm not her mother,
if that's what you're asking.
- You act like it.

646
01:11:57,152 --> 01:11:59,382
What are those marks
on her back ?

647
01:11:59,454 --> 01:12:02,116
Nothing.
They're just fanciful things.

648
01:12:03,425 --> 01:12:07,555
- Like what she draws ?
- She draws what she sees.

649
01:12:07,629 --> 01:12:10,462
She's like a mirror.

650
01:12:10,532 --> 01:12:12,591
People on the atoll
thought she was a--

651
01:12:14,369 --> 01:12:17,099
Freak ?

652
01:12:17,172 --> 01:12:19,572
Uh-huh. Yeah.

653
01:12:19,641 --> 01:12:21,609
l just thought
she was special.

654
01:12:29,317 --> 01:12:33,117
l'm not givin' it
to her. lt's just--

655
01:12:33,188 --> 01:12:34,951
A loan.

656
01:12:35,023 --> 01:12:37,992
Yeah. l'm not
givin' it to her.

657
01:12:43,798 --> 01:12:46,995
ls Dryland beautiful ?

658
01:12:48,537 --> 01:12:50,903
You'll see.

659
01:13:08,690 --> 01:13:13,627
[ Enola Laughing, Giggling ]

660
01:13:16,665 --> 01:13:19,099
- Enola ?
- [ Laughing ]

661
01:13:19,167 --> 01:13:21,158
Enola, what are you doing ?

662
01:13:21,236 --> 01:13:24,672
- Those monsters'll kill her !
- No, they're asleep now.

663
01:13:28,035 --> 01:13:29,832
Hands around my neck.

664
01:13:31,872 --> 01:13:35,411
Let the water tell your arms
and legs how to move.

665
01:13:35,544 --> 01:13:36,533
We're goin' down.
Hold your breath.

666
01:15:16,042 --> 01:15:19,034
- What is it ?
- What is it ?

667
01:15:21,113 --> 01:15:23,206
Barter outpost.

668
01:15:23,282 --> 01:15:25,250
You said we'd get
to Dryland today.

669
01:15:25,317 --> 01:15:28,445
Today. Tomorrow.
What's it matter ?

670
01:15:30,089 --> 01:15:32,023
l need resin.

671
01:15:41,667 --> 01:15:47,071
- What is that ?
- lt's PortuGreek. Their own language.

672
01:15:50,042 --> 01:15:52,374
Or so l thought.

673
01:16:18,804 --> 01:16:21,068
Ah.

674
01:16:21,140 --> 01:16:24,473
There's my girl. Yeah.

675
01:16:24,543 --> 01:16:28,172
Howdy, darlin'.
Come on in here now.

676
01:16:57,743 --> 01:17:00,109
- What's going on ?
- Smokers.

677
01:17:03,516 --> 01:17:05,450
What the hell ?

678
01:17:09,021 --> 01:17:11,956
He's spotted us.
Sound it !

679
01:17:12,024 --> 01:17:15,858
Sound it ! Sound it !
Sound it ! Sound it !

680
01:17:26,906 --> 01:17:29,500
Yahoo !

681
01:17:37,316 --> 01:17:40,376
[ Helen ] Enola !

682
01:17:48,961 --> 01:17:51,828
- [ Bullets Whizzing By ]
- [ Grunting ]

683
01:17:51,897 --> 01:17:53,888
Starboard side ! Now !

684
01:17:54,967 --> 01:17:56,901
Get in the chair !

685
01:18:03,242 --> 01:18:06,109
Watch it.
He's clearin' the net.

686
01:18:17,523 --> 01:18:19,684
Go to the helm.

687
01:18:21,493 --> 01:18:23,859
- Get the centerboard !
- Centerboard ?

688
01:18:23,929 --> 01:18:26,693
What centerboard ?
l don't know what to do !

689
01:18:29,301 --> 01:18:31,360
lt's too late.
Over here !

690
01:18:44,383 --> 01:18:48,012
[ Screaming, Yelling ]

691
01:18:50,956 --> 01:18:52,924
No !

692
01:19:09,208 --> 01:19:14,077
Gimme that rifle.
Boy, if you wanna do somethin' right,

693
01:19:14,146 --> 01:19:16,808
you've got to do it yourself.

694
01:19:16,882 --> 01:19:18,816
[ Whispers ]
All right.

695
01:19:25,391 --> 01:19:27,325
- l winged him.
- l say we load...

696
01:19:27,393 --> 01:19:30,556
all the go-juice onto one boat
and run the freak down.

697
01:19:30,629 --> 01:19:33,928
You can't catch him in ten boats,
and you wanna send just one ?

698
01:19:33,999 --> 01:19:36,627
Well, l pray that you're jokin'.

699
01:19:45,044 --> 01:19:48,104
Bring me the trackers.

700
01:19:52,851 --> 01:19:55,319
He's hurt.

701
01:19:55,387 --> 01:19:57,753
lt's not what you think.
They weren't after her.

702
01:19:57,823 --> 01:20:00,451
- l saw what l saw.
- What ?

703
01:20:04,830 --> 01:20:06,764
No more lies.

704
01:20:08,233 --> 01:20:11,464
- [ Shrieks ]
- What are the marks on her back ?

705
01:20:11,537 --> 01:20:14,199
People say it's the way to Dryland.

706
01:20:14,273 --> 01:20:16,867
Dryland's a myth !

707
01:20:16,942 --> 01:20:19,968
No ! You said so yourself
that you know where it is.

708
01:20:20,045 --> 01:20:21,979
You did.

709
01:20:26,185 --> 01:20:29,382
You're a fool to believe in something
you've never seen before.

710
01:20:29,455 --> 01:20:33,892
l've seen it. l've touched it !
Dirt that was richer
and darker than yours.

711
01:20:33,959 --> 01:20:35,859
lt was in the basket
we found Enola in !

712
01:20:35,928 --> 01:20:38,556
- lt doesn't exist !
- Well, how can you be so sure ?

713
01:20:38,630 --> 01:20:43,363
Because l've sailed farther than most
have dreamed, and l've never seen it.

714
01:20:45,304 --> 01:20:48,102
But the things on your boat !

715
01:20:48,173 --> 01:20:50,573
''Things on my boat'' what ?

716
01:20:50,642 --> 01:20:54,078
There are things on your boat
that nobody has ever seen !

717
01:20:54,146 --> 01:20:56,307
What are these shells ?

718
01:20:56,382 --> 01:20:59,510
And that reflecting glass ?

719
01:20:59,585 --> 01:21:03,954
And th-the music box ?
That--

720
01:21:04,022 --> 01:21:07,719
Well, if not from Dryland,
then where ? Wh-Where ?

721
01:21:10,596 --> 01:21:12,564
You wanna see Dryland ?

722
01:21:14,266 --> 01:21:16,200
You really wanna see it ?

723
01:21:17,870 --> 01:21:19,929
l'll take you to Dryland.

724
01:21:27,279 --> 01:21:29,213
Get in.

725
01:21:35,187 --> 01:21:38,315
- Well, what about Enola ?
- There's only air for one.

726
01:21:38,390 --> 01:21:40,722
- Get in the water.
- lt'll be all right.

727
01:21:46,365 --> 01:21:48,424
Don't touch anything.

728
01:21:53,205 --> 01:21:55,139
Okay ?

729
01:25:26,223 --> 01:25:28,157
l didn't know.

730
01:25:29,994 --> 01:25:32,986
All this time...

731
01:25:33,063 --> 01:25:34,997
l didn't know.

732
01:25:35,065 --> 01:25:36,999
Nobody does.

733
01:25:45,075 --> 01:25:47,043
Can you get us outta here ?

734
01:25:47,111 --> 01:25:50,603
l'd say there're
two chances o' that.

735
01:25:50,681 --> 01:25:53,115
- Hey !
- No way and no how.

736
01:25:53,184 --> 01:25:56,915
Shoulda bought me
that drink. Come on !

737
01:25:56,987 --> 01:25:58,784
This way. Come on !

738
01:25:58,856 --> 01:26:03,691
[ Men Yelling, Cheering ]

739
01:26:05,529 --> 01:26:07,793
Proper introductions first.

740
01:26:08,899 --> 01:26:11,367
l'm the Deacon.

741
01:26:11,435 --> 01:26:15,633
[ Men Laughing ]

742
01:26:15,706 --> 01:26:20,405
lf you don't recall the face,
perhaps it's 'cause l didn't
always look like this.

743
01:26:23,547 --> 01:26:27,176
Now, ahem, l suspect
she's somewhere real close.

744
01:26:27,251 --> 01:26:33,121
So we can tear this boat apart
lookin' for her, but l'd rather
somebody tell me where she is.

745
01:26:33,190 --> 01:26:36,023
And the first one
that does that, lives.

746
01:26:36,093 --> 01:26:40,496
And the runner-up--
Well, actually, there are no runners-up.

747
01:26:43,100 --> 01:26:45,728
Oh, sweet Joe,
l love this part.

748
01:26:45,803 --> 01:26:48,670
Choose 'em. One, two.
Live or die.

749
01:26:50,174 --> 01:26:53,337
You know, personally,

750
01:26:53,410 --> 01:26:56,345
l'd rather shoot
the sperm-of-the-devil here.

751
01:26:56,413 --> 01:26:59,644
Huh ? But you know somethin' ?

752
01:26:59,717 --> 01:27:02,208
l don't think you're gonna
tell me, are ya ?

753
01:27:02,286 --> 01:27:04,220
Huh ? Too bad.

754
01:27:05,356 --> 01:27:08,848
Come on, eh ?
What do you say ?

755
01:27:08,926 --> 01:27:10,860
She's not your kind.

756
01:27:12,329 --> 01:27:14,820
You don't even have a kind.

757
01:27:14,899 --> 01:27:19,029
lf you say it,
he'll still kill us both.

758
01:27:19,103 --> 01:27:22,197
[ Deacon Grunts ]

759
01:27:23,374 --> 01:27:25,308
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

760
01:27:27,344 --> 01:27:29,278
lf you don't tell me,

761
01:27:29,346 --> 01:27:31,906
l swear to Poseidon
l will torch your boat.

762
01:27:38,522 --> 01:27:41,980
Refresh my memory.
What happens when neither of 'em talks ?

763
01:27:42,059 --> 01:27:44,892
- Never happened before.
- Never happened before.

764
01:27:44,962 --> 01:27:47,590
[ Sighs ]
All right !

765
01:27:47,665 --> 01:27:52,762
lf they won't tell us where
she is, do 'em ! Both of 'em !
Kill 'em now ! [ Fires Gun ]

766
01:27:52,836 --> 01:27:55,737
- No !
- [ Helen ] No !

767
01:27:55,806 --> 01:27:57,740
So gullible !
Bring her here.

768
01:27:57,808 --> 01:28:00,242
[ Men Cheering, Shouting ]

769
01:28:00,311 --> 01:28:03,041
- Take and ye shall receive !
- [ Helen ] No ! Leave her !

770
01:28:03,113 --> 01:28:05,775
So ends your daily sermonette !
[ Laughing ]

771
01:28:05,849 --> 01:28:09,717
All we gotta do is figure out this map.
Turn her upside down.

772
01:28:09,787 --> 01:28:13,120
-Does that mean anything to you ?
-No.

773
01:28:13,190 --> 01:28:16,717
[ Deacon ] We'll figure it out back
at the 'Deez. Back at the 'Deez, boys.

774
01:28:16,794 --> 01:28:19,126
Careful with her.
Careful with her !

775
01:28:19,196 --> 01:28:21,096
- What about them ?
- Do 'em both.

776
01:28:21,165 --> 01:28:23,759
Torch the boat.

777
01:28:27,204 --> 01:28:30,139
We have to go under !

778
01:28:31,275 --> 01:28:34,142
No, l can't breath like you !

779
01:28:34,211 --> 01:28:36,145
l'll breathe for both of us.

780
01:29:00,771 --> 01:29:02,705
[ Man ] Whoo !

781
01:29:02,773 --> 01:29:04,707
[ Enola ] Helen !

782
01:29:06,744 --> 01:29:12,307
Helen, help !
Helen ! Helen !

783
01:29:43,480 --> 01:29:45,414
My boat.

784
01:29:54,858 --> 01:29:56,792
Enola.

785
01:29:56,860 --> 01:29:59,090
[ Door Opens ]

786
01:29:59,163 --> 01:30:01,996
What is this ?
Get those chains off her.

787
01:30:02,066 --> 01:30:05,001
What are we, barbarians here ?

788
01:30:05,069 --> 01:30:07,469
Goodness gracious.
Sakes alive.

789
01:30:07,538 --> 01:30:09,972
Come on. Outta here,
you big, nasty animal, you !

790
01:30:11,675 --> 01:30:14,075
Well, rub-a-dub-dub.
[ Chuckles ]

791
01:30:15,979 --> 01:30:19,380
You wanna come over here
and sit on my lap ?

792
01:30:19,450 --> 01:30:22,180
No ? Ahem.

793
01:30:22,252 --> 01:30:25,244
How 'bout a cigarette ?

794
01:30:25,322 --> 01:30:28,758
Nothin' like a good smoke
if you miss your mom.

795
01:30:28,826 --> 01:30:30,760
Never too young to start.

796
01:30:32,396 --> 01:30:35,763
No. Well, l got somethin'
right here l know you'd like.

797
01:30:37,534 --> 01:30:40,059
Like to draw, don't you ? Huh ?

798
01:30:42,072 --> 01:30:46,270
Huh ?
Now they're yours...

799
01:30:46,343 --> 01:30:50,609
if you help me with just
one problem, all right ?

800
01:30:53,617 --> 01:30:57,212
Now, ahem-- Now that tattoo
on your back-- Ahem.

801
01:30:58,922 --> 01:31:03,359
l've been told that, uh--
that's actually a map ?

802
01:31:06,563 --> 01:31:08,929
lt's the way to Dryland.

803
01:31:08,999 --> 01:31:10,933
Now we're gettin' someplace.

804
01:31:12,736 --> 01:31:15,500
Could you teach me
how to read that ?

805
01:31:18,408 --> 01:31:20,342
Setback.

806
01:31:22,546 --> 01:31:26,676
Well, have you ever heard
any of your friends talk about it ?

807
01:31:26,750 --> 01:31:31,881
You know, like your mommy or
your pet fish ? Did he say anything ?

808
01:31:31,955 --> 01:31:34,389
You shouldn't make fun of him.
He wouldn't like it.

809
01:31:34,458 --> 01:31:39,862
Girl, l don't give a shit
what he'd like. He took out my eye.

810
01:31:39,930 --> 01:31:45,869
And if l ever see him again, l'm gonna
cut open his head and eat his brains !

811
01:31:45,936 --> 01:31:48,166
You think he'd like that ?

812
01:31:48,238 --> 01:31:52,019
Can't kill him.
He's even meaner than you are.

813
01:31:53,020 --> 01:31:55,181
But he's not here.

814
01:31:55,255 --> 01:31:57,189
And he ain't comin'.

815
01:31:57,257 --> 01:31:59,122
And no one's gonna save you.

816
01:32:00,527 --> 01:32:02,461
He'll come for me. He will.

817
01:32:02,529 --> 01:32:06,590
Then you better tell me what l wanna
know or he can see what's left of you...

818
01:32:06,667 --> 01:32:08,828
in a goddamn jar.

819
01:32:19,146 --> 01:32:21,512
We're going to die here,
aren't we ?

820
01:32:41,401 --> 01:32:43,335
Aren't we ?

821
01:32:52,779 --> 01:32:55,475
After the atoll,

822
01:32:55,549 --> 01:32:58,211
when l offered myself to you,

823
01:33:00,821 --> 01:33:03,289
why didn't you take me ?

824
01:33:05,158 --> 01:33:07,092
'Cause you didn't really want me.

825
01:33:09,062 --> 01:33:12,054
Not really.

826
01:35:07,814 --> 01:35:10,146
Have l been asleep long ?

827
01:35:15,856 --> 01:35:17,790
l was dreaming.

828
01:35:20,293 --> 01:35:23,285
lt's funny.

829
01:35:23,363 --> 01:35:26,093
l always thought Dryland floated.

830
01:35:26,166 --> 01:35:29,567
That it drifted with the wind.
That's why it was so hard to find.

831
01:35:29,636 --> 01:35:31,900
Why did you believe in it so much ?

832
01:35:33,206 --> 01:35:35,766
Because we weren't made for the sea.

833
01:35:37,077 --> 01:35:40,342
Got hands... and feet.

834
01:35:40,413 --> 01:35:43,041
We're supposed to walk.

835
01:35:46,086 --> 01:35:48,020
l miss her sound.

836
01:35:50,557 --> 01:35:52,491
Don't you ?

837
01:35:55,996 --> 01:35:57,861
[ Gregor ] Helen !

838
01:35:57,931 --> 01:36:01,094
He-- No, no, no.
Helen, up here. Above you !

839
01:36:01,167 --> 01:36:03,727
- [ Chuckling ]
- [ Helen ] Gregor !

840
01:36:03,803 --> 01:36:08,001
[ Chuckling Continues ]

841
01:36:08,074 --> 01:36:10,838
Smart thinking
to burn your boat.

842
01:36:10,911 --> 01:36:14,677
Without the smoke,
l never would have found you.

843
01:36:14,748 --> 01:36:16,773
Who's that with you ?

844
01:36:16,850 --> 01:36:20,547
lchthyus Sapien,
is that really you ?

845
01:36:20,620 --> 01:36:24,579
l'll throw the rope down.
You catch it. l'll help you climb up.

846
01:36:26,826 --> 01:36:30,284
Helen. Where's Enola ?

847
01:36:30,363 --> 01:36:35,767
Smokers took her. They'd have me too
if it weren't for him.

848
01:36:35,835 --> 01:36:40,033
My friend, thank you.
Very human of you.

849
01:36:42,008 --> 01:36:44,670
Go grab your things quickly.
Quickly. Come.

850
01:36:52,552 --> 01:36:54,577
[ Gregor ] You see ?
Right down there.

851
01:36:54,654 --> 01:36:57,646
There's several of us survivors.
We'll just start over again.

852
01:36:59,726 --> 01:37:01,660
[ Man ] You can't ask us
to go get her !

853
01:37:01,728 --> 01:37:03,958
[ Woman ] Enola's the reason
we're in all this trouble.

854
01:37:04,030 --> 01:37:08,797
[ Helen ] They don't have any
reason to kill her. They need
to find Dryland just like we do.

855
01:37:08,868 --> 01:37:12,827
- Of course.
- [ Helen ] lf the Mariner's
willing to go, why not us ?

856
01:37:12,906 --> 01:37:14,999
[ Woman ]
lf he wants to go, then let him !

857
01:37:15,075 --> 01:37:18,306
[ Woman #2 ] We don't want you here !
You or the girl !

858
01:37:18,378 --> 01:37:22,815
Helen. The papers
the Mariner brought you--

859
01:37:22,882 --> 01:37:27,512
lt's the same language the tattoo
is written in. They're numbers.

860
01:37:27,587 --> 01:37:30,886
- [ Man ] Gregor,
you're as crazy as she is !
- [ Woman ] We can't stay here !

861
01:37:30,957 --> 01:37:34,552
We're wasting valuable time.
More Smokers will come.
We need to be moving now !

862
01:37:34,628 --> 01:37:38,997
My friends, don't you see we need
this child if we want to find Dryland ?

863
01:37:39,065 --> 01:37:41,033
- l'm not goin'.
- Nobody is.

864
01:37:41,101 --> 01:37:43,501
[ Woman ] We've seen their smoke
on the horizon !

865
01:37:43,570 --> 01:37:46,334
- Know what that is yet ?
- The numbers ? Yes, l think l do.

866
01:37:46,406 --> 01:37:51,935
lt seems to be some ancient form
of geographic location:
latitude, longitude.

867
01:37:52,012 --> 01:37:56,847
lt doesn't make sense, though.
The numbers, they seem
to be backwards or something.

868
01:37:56,916 --> 01:37:59,077
- lt's upside down.
- The world ?

869
01:37:59,152 --> 01:38:01,780
The poles have reversed themselves ?

870
01:38:01,855 --> 01:38:04,119
l've been mappin' the cities below.

871
01:38:06,926 --> 01:38:10,327
The world wasn't created in a deluge.
lt was covered by it.

872
01:38:10,397 --> 01:38:13,628
- [ Man ] That's blasphemy !
- [ Helen ] No, it's true.

873
01:38:13,700 --> 01:38:18,399
l've seen it with
my own eyes. There is land.
lt's right under our keel.

874
01:38:18,471 --> 01:38:20,564
- None of it's dry anymore.
- Some is.

875
01:38:22,042 --> 01:38:26,638
Enola's been there.
l know that now. l saw what she drew.

876
01:38:26,713 --> 01:38:30,547
So that's why he's going after Enola--
to find Dryland.

877
01:38:30,617 --> 01:38:33,313
l don't care about Dryland.

878
01:38:33,386 --> 01:38:36,219
This is ridiculous.
Going after the Smokers ?

879
01:38:36,289 --> 01:38:38,553
He doesn't even know
which direction they came from.

880
01:38:38,625 --> 01:38:43,460
- [ Man ] l say let him go.
- [ Woman ] We're better off
without them anyway !

881
01:38:43,530 --> 01:38:47,261
lf she's alive,
l'll bring her back to you.

882
01:38:47,333 --> 01:38:51,929
[ Woman ] Forget the mute-o, Helen.
lf he brings her back, they'll kill us !

883
01:38:52,005 --> 01:38:55,668
l can't stand it. We gotta go help him.
l can't ask him to do this alone.

884
01:38:55,742 --> 01:38:59,769
Oh, don't worry, my dear.
You're not going to have to.

885
01:39:05,686 --> 01:39:08,621
[ Deacon ] You got that tattoo
figured out yet ?

886
01:39:08,689 --> 01:39:11,283
lt would be easier if it was flat--
big and flat.

887
01:39:11,358 --> 01:39:14,225
- lt needs to be flat.
- What you got in mind ?

888
01:39:14,295 --> 01:39:18,629
Well, you cut it off her back.
You stretch it, mount it.

889
01:39:18,699 --> 01:39:22,362
- Give us a proper look.
- Take her down below until l holler.

890
01:39:22,436 --> 01:39:24,666
Saint Joe, we're close.

891
01:39:26,941 --> 01:39:29,273
After centuries of shame.

892
01:40:05,379 --> 01:40:07,438
[ Scraping ]

893
01:40:15,222 --> 01:40:18,191
[ Distant Shouting ]

894
01:40:49,790 --> 01:40:53,317
[ Distant Laughter ]

895
01:40:56,163 --> 01:40:59,599
[ Crowd Shouting ]

896
01:40:59,666 --> 01:41:03,329
- They're gettin' ugly.
- Don't l know it.

897
01:41:03,404 --> 01:41:05,429
Announce me, cousin.

898
01:41:07,174 --> 01:41:09,438
[ Crowd Chanting ]

899
01:41:09,510 --> 01:41:11,603
- [ Microphone Popping ]
- Hey. Here he is.

900
01:41:11,678 --> 01:41:13,612
[ Crowd ] Deacon !

901
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:16,205
Rise up, brothers and sisters.

902
01:41:17,885 --> 01:41:21,321
Turn your eyes and open your hearts...

903
01:41:21,388 --> 01:41:23,822
to your humble benefactor,

904
01:41:23,891 --> 01:41:27,759
your spiritual shepherd
and dictator for life,

905
01:41:27,828 --> 01:41:30,820
the Deacon of the 'Deez.

906
01:41:30,898 --> 01:41:33,833
[ Crowd Cheering ]

907
01:41:47,581 --> 01:41:50,072
[ Cheering Continues ]

908
01:41:52,386 --> 01:41:55,514
- Look out !
- lt's mine ! lt's mine !

909
01:41:55,589 --> 01:41:57,955
[ Confused Shouting ]

910
01:42:02,162 --> 01:42:05,529
- Deacon !
- Wahoo !

911
01:42:05,599 --> 01:42:11,367
Children.
Children of the provider.

912
01:42:11,438 --> 01:42:15,306
Citizens of the good ship.
Please now, hear me speak.

913
01:42:19,313 --> 01:42:22,407
- l've had a vision.
- [ Man ] Yeah, we're
tired of your visions !

914
01:42:22,483 --> 01:42:24,849
What about the land
you promised us ?

915
01:42:24,918 --> 01:42:27,682
[ Crowd ]
Yeah ! Yeah !

916
01:42:27,754 --> 01:42:29,949
[ Deacon ]
O ye of little faith.

917
01:42:30,023 --> 01:42:32,287
l've had a vision so great...

918
01:42:32,359 --> 01:42:35,760
that as it came to me, l wept.

919
01:42:35,829 --> 01:42:39,959
- And in this splenditudinous
figment of wonder,
- ls that Bone's ride ?

920
01:42:40,033 --> 01:42:42,126
- ls that blood on the seat ?
- l saw--

921
01:42:42,202 --> 01:42:46,070
And you know
what it is that l saw.

922
01:42:46,140 --> 01:42:50,042
l saw... the land.

923
01:42:50,110 --> 01:42:53,102
[ Cheering ]

924
01:43:00,354 --> 01:43:03,915
[ Gasping ]

925
01:43:15,235 --> 01:43:17,430
[ Crowd Chanting ]

926
01:43:23,143 --> 01:43:25,304
- Horse, that you ?
- [ Engine Revving ]

927
01:43:29,983 --> 01:43:33,111
Look, just bring it in slow,
okay ? l don't have all day.

928
01:43:33,187 --> 01:43:36,554
- [ Engine Revs ]
- Horse !

929
01:43:36,623 --> 01:43:39,114
Just bring it up slow.

930
01:43:40,227 --> 01:43:43,128
l said slow !
[ Screams ]

931
01:43:47,701 --> 01:43:51,899
Shouldn't be doing that.
You're gonna get in trouble.

932
01:43:51,972 --> 01:43:54,236
Ha. That's right.

933
01:43:54,308 --> 01:43:58,335
You're not afraid. You've got
your pet freak comin' to rescue you.

934
01:43:58,412 --> 01:44:02,974
He's not a freak,
and he can take you anytime.

935
01:44:03,050 --> 01:44:07,146
He's killed dozens of people, and he
doesn't have any mercy or anything.

936
01:44:07,221 --> 01:44:09,348
He even kills little girls.

937
01:44:11,225 --> 01:44:12,817
Haven't we all ?

938
01:44:14,895 --> 01:44:16,886
Shit.

939
01:44:16,964 --> 01:44:19,159
lt's Horse.

940
01:44:20,500 --> 01:44:22,991
- Find him. Find him !
- Come on !

941
01:44:23,070 --> 01:44:27,370
- [ Crowd Chanting ]
- Yes ! Yes ! Yes !

942
01:44:27,441 --> 01:44:31,104
- Come on.
- Gettin' nervous, aren't you ?

943
01:44:35,415 --> 01:44:37,349
l don't get nervous.

944
01:44:38,652 --> 01:44:41,177
[ Deacon ]
And if there's a river, we'll dam it.

945
01:44:41,255 --> 01:44:45,715
And if there's a tree,
we'll ram it.

946
01:44:45,792 --> 01:44:48,920
'Cause l'm talkin' progress here.

947
01:44:48,996 --> 01:44:52,022
Yes, sir. l'm talkin' development.

948
01:44:52,099 --> 01:44:56,126
- [ Man ] Yeah !
- For we shall suck and savor...

949
01:44:56,203 --> 01:45:00,640
the sweet flavor of Dryland.

950
01:45:00,707 --> 01:45:02,572
- [ Crowd Whistling ]
- [ Enola ] Face is all red.

951
01:45:02,643 --> 01:45:07,740
- [ Deacon Continues Faintly ]
- Helen said with anybody
that has a face that red,

952
01:45:07,814 --> 01:45:09,975
he's had too much sun
or too much to drink.

953
01:45:10,050 --> 01:45:14,146
- All right, that's it.
l'm gonna burn your face.
- Almost time.

954
01:45:14,221 --> 01:45:18,317
- [ Clanging ]
- What's up ?
- We're just talkin' about our friend.

955
01:45:20,661 --> 01:45:23,528
- [ Doctor ] What's his name ?
- [ Enola ] He doesn't have a name.

956
01:45:23,597 --> 01:45:26,191
So death can't find him.

957
01:45:26,266 --> 01:45:28,200
Nah-nah.

958
01:45:31,471 --> 01:45:35,407
Doesn't have a home
or people to care for.

959
01:45:35,475 --> 01:45:38,410
He's not afraid of anything,
men least of all.

960
01:45:38,478 --> 01:45:42,107
He's fast and strong
like a big wind.

961
01:45:42,182 --> 01:45:45,413
He can hear a hundred miles
and see a hundred miles underwater.

962
01:45:45,485 --> 01:45:49,512
- [ Gagging ]
- He can hide in the shadow
of the noon sun.

963
01:45:49,589 --> 01:45:53,491
He could be right behind you, and you
won't even know it 'til you're dead !

964
01:45:56,063 --> 01:45:58,088
Give it a rest.

965
01:45:59,366 --> 01:46:01,391
He'll come for me. He will.

966
01:46:01,468 --> 01:46:04,062
- [ Deacon Addressing Crowd ]
We are the people--
- Yeah ?

967
01:46:04,137 --> 01:46:07,573
- Well, l hope he does.
- [ Deacon ] The Lord's creation.

968
01:46:08,875 --> 01:46:10,809
Remember you said that.

969
01:46:11,945 --> 01:46:14,709
[ Deacon Continues ]
Look at us.

970
01:46:14,781 --> 01:46:17,409
- Look at us here today.
- [ Man ] Yeah !

971
01:46:17,484 --> 01:46:21,113
Dryland is not just
our destination,

972
01:46:21,188 --> 01:46:23,281
but it is our destiny !

973
01:46:23,357 --> 01:46:25,655
[ Cheering, Whistling ]

974
01:46:32,666 --> 01:46:35,134
Find him. Find him !

975
01:46:35,202 --> 01:46:37,363
How can l find...

976
01:46:37,437 --> 01:46:39,564
this glorious place ?

977
01:46:40,640 --> 01:46:43,438
And he said to me:

978
01:46:43,510 --> 01:46:47,469
''A child shall lead you.''

979
01:46:48,949 --> 01:46:51,076
A child.

980
01:46:51,151 --> 01:46:53,449
- And behold !
- lt's time.

981
01:46:53,520 --> 01:46:56,580
The instrument of our salvation !

982
01:46:56,656 --> 01:47:00,490
[ Crowd Cheering ]

983
01:47:04,097 --> 01:47:06,531
[ Deacon ]
Our guide in the wild.

984
01:47:06,600 --> 01:47:09,000
[ Deacon ]
Our beacon in the darkness.

985
01:47:09,069 --> 01:47:11,003
Turn her around, Nord.

986
01:47:11,071 --> 01:47:13,869
She has shown me the path !

987
01:47:13,940 --> 01:47:16,500
[ Cheering ]

988
01:47:18,345 --> 01:47:21,803
And before the holy-most moment
is upon us,

989
01:47:21,882 --> 01:47:25,340
let's sacrifice one
to old Saint Joe.

990
01:47:28,522 --> 01:47:32,117
And let's get this
tub of shit up to speed.

991
01:47:38,198 --> 01:47:40,166
Yep.

992
01:47:47,841 --> 01:47:50,776
[ Wild Cheering ]

993
01:48:18,171 --> 01:48:20,105
Pull !

994
01:48:20,173 --> 01:48:22,835
- Pull !
- Pull !

995
01:48:22,909 --> 01:48:25,036
- Pull.
- Pull !

996
01:48:39,559 --> 01:48:41,493
Ow.

997
01:48:45,031 --> 01:48:48,330
- So which way we rowin' ?
- l don't have a goddamn clue.

998
01:48:48,401 --> 01:48:50,335
[ Laughs ]
Don't worry.

999
01:48:50,403 --> 01:48:53,372
They'll row for a month
before they figure out l'm fakin' it.

1000
01:48:53,440 --> 01:48:56,102
But, um, wh-wh--

1001
01:48:56,176 --> 01:48:59,304
Oh, you want details.
Well, l'm not tellin' these savages...

1002
01:48:59,379 --> 01:49:01,574
that we haven't
solved the map yet.

1003
01:49:01,648 --> 01:49:07,097
l promised them results,
and l'll get 'em if l gotta
cut 'em out of her goddamn back.

1004
01:49:08,465 --> 01:49:11,832
Who is that ?
Who is that ?

1005
01:49:12,936 --> 01:49:15,404
Maybe one of
the spare rowers ?

1006
01:49:23,313 --> 01:49:26,043
Why aren't you rowin' ?

1007
01:49:34,624 --> 01:49:36,717
- lt's him.
- lt is him.

1008
01:49:38,128 --> 01:49:40,790
You guys are in
so much trouble.

1009
01:49:43,633 --> 01:49:48,002
Well, l'll be damned.
lt's the gentleman guppy.

1010
01:49:48,071 --> 01:49:51,871
You know, he's like
a turd that won't flush.

1011
01:49:51,941 --> 01:49:54,603
l want the girl.

1012
01:49:57,013 --> 01:50:02,178
You know, l thought you
were stupid, friend.

1013
01:50:02,252 --> 01:50:05,187
- [ Gun Cocking ]
- But l underestimated you.

1014
01:50:05,255 --> 01:50:08,281
You're a total freakin' retard.

1015
01:50:08,358 --> 01:50:11,418
[ Laughing ]

1016
01:50:11,494 --> 01:50:14,725
l want the girl. That's all.

1017
01:50:14,798 --> 01:50:19,599
Well, what on this screwed-up Earth
makes you think you're gonna get her ?

1018
01:50:27,877 --> 01:50:29,811
You know what this is ?

1019
01:50:34,150 --> 01:50:36,641
l drop it, you burn.

1020
01:50:36,719 --> 01:50:40,621
- We all burn.
- Now wait, wait, wait, wait.

1021
01:50:40,690 --> 01:50:44,524
Ahem. Let's not do
anything rash here.

1022
01:50:44,594 --> 01:50:47,791
l mean, uh, are you sure
she's worth all this ?

1023
01:50:47,864 --> 01:50:51,027
She never does stop talkin'.
She never shuts up.

1024
01:50:51,100 --> 01:50:53,432
- l noticed.
- What is it then ?

1025
01:50:53,503 --> 01:50:55,835
Huh ? lt's the map.

1026
01:50:57,340 --> 01:51:00,104
She's my friend.

1027
01:51:00,176 --> 01:51:02,940
Golly gee.
A single tear rolls down my cheek.

1028
01:51:03,012 --> 01:51:05,947
l mean, you're gonna
die for your friend.

1029
01:51:07,350 --> 01:51:09,284
lf it comes to that.

1030
01:51:11,588 --> 01:51:16,025
- He's bluffing. l'll kill him.
- He's not bluffing. He never bluffs.

1031
01:51:16,092 --> 01:51:17,286
Shut up !

1032
01:51:18,628 --> 01:51:23,793
l don't-- l-l-- l don't think
you're gonna drop that torch, my friend.

1033
01:51:23,867 --> 01:51:27,530
- Why not ?
- Because you're not crazy.

1034
01:51:31,074 --> 01:51:33,872
No !

1035
01:51:40,817 --> 01:51:43,547
Oh, thank God.

1036
01:51:47,323 --> 01:51:50,053
[ Screaming ]

1037
01:51:55,298 --> 01:51:58,426
[ Gunfire ]

1038
01:52:00,470 --> 01:52:02,768
[ Smoker ]
Look out ! [ Screaming ]

1039
01:52:02,839 --> 01:52:05,330
Get him !

1040
01:52:05,408 --> 01:52:08,900
Let's go, goddamn it !

1041
01:52:08,978 --> 01:52:13,711
- [ Screaming ]
- Don't just stand there !
Kill somethin' !

1042
01:52:16,886 --> 01:52:18,820
Was this your big vision ?

1043
01:52:22,792 --> 01:52:25,693
[ Screaming ]

1044
01:52:27,530 --> 01:52:31,466
Oh, yeah ! l've always wanted
to drive this monster.

1045
01:52:34,737 --> 01:52:37,934
There he is !
There he is !

1046
01:52:41,010 --> 01:52:43,376
That's him ! There !

1047
01:52:45,615 --> 01:52:48,106
[ Shrieks ]

1048
01:52:50,486 --> 01:52:53,478
[ Screaming ]

1049
01:52:56,292 --> 01:52:59,887
[ Enola ]
No ! Let go !

1050
01:53:05,702 --> 01:53:07,636
[ Explosion ]

1051
01:53:09,572 --> 01:53:11,972
[ Enola ]
Let go !

1052
01:53:15,378 --> 01:53:17,938
- [ Enola ] Let me go ! Let go !
- [ Deacon ] Pilot !

1053
01:53:18,014 --> 01:53:20,482
- [ Deacon ] Pilot !
- [ Enola ] Let me go !

1054
01:53:20,550 --> 01:53:22,484
- [ Mariner Cocking Gun ]
- Let go !

1055
01:53:22,552 --> 01:53:24,520
Let go-o-o-o !

1056
01:53:26,823 --> 01:53:29,724
[ Laughing ]
You should've stayed underwater.

1057
01:53:29,792 --> 01:53:32,693
[ Clicks Twice ]

1058
01:53:35,164 --> 01:53:37,860
Oh !

1059
01:53:39,502 --> 01:53:43,836
Now you know how to fly an airplane ?
You're lucky l do.

1060
01:53:43,906 --> 01:53:46,898
Ow ! Now you stop it !
You behave yourself now !

1061
01:54:17,940 --> 01:54:20,170
[ Explosions ]

1062
01:54:41,964 --> 01:54:44,990
- Oh !
- [ Mariner Grunting ]

1063
01:54:57,513 --> 01:54:59,743
[ Explosion ]

1064
01:55:12,595 --> 01:55:14,529
[ Explosion ]

1065
01:55:19,368 --> 01:55:21,302
[ Helen ]
lt's going down.

1066
01:55:21,370 --> 01:55:26,569
- You can see it sinking.
- Gregor, bring us
right down on top of it.

1067
01:55:26,642 --> 01:55:28,803
- Hurry, Gregor !
- [ Gregor ] Don't worry.

1068
01:55:28,878 --> 01:55:30,812
Hurry.

1069
01:55:34,784 --> 01:55:37,810
[ Clanging, Rumbling ]

1070
01:55:42,558 --> 01:55:45,721
Enola ! Up here !

1071
01:55:45,795 --> 01:55:47,786
Grab on !

1072
01:55:52,869 --> 01:55:54,837
[ Gregor ]
Are they on yet ?

1073
01:55:58,207 --> 01:56:01,005
- [ Gregor ] What is it ?
- [ Helen ] l don't know !

1074
01:56:01,077 --> 01:56:02,874
No !

1075
01:56:12,121 --> 01:56:17,559
Gotcha ! l'm gonna rip
your cute little lungs out.

1076
01:56:21,230 --> 01:56:23,198
[ Yelling ]

1077
01:56:26,636 --> 01:56:29,264
[ Enraged Shout ]

1078
01:56:31,841 --> 01:56:34,366
Pull ! Almost.

1079
01:56:38,214 --> 01:56:40,808
[ Helen, Gregor Laughing ]

1080
01:56:42,218 --> 01:56:45,881
[ Explosion ]

1081
01:57:13,417 --> 01:57:15,146
- [ Shrieks ]
- [ Helen ] No !

1082
01:57:15,218 --> 01:57:18,153
- [ Enola Screaming ]
- [ Helen ] No ! Enola !

1083
01:57:19,523 --> 01:57:21,957
Saint Joe.
Hole in one.

1084
01:57:22,025 --> 01:57:25,825
- Helen !
- [ Helen ] No ! Enola !
- [ Gregor ] Helen !

1085
01:57:25,896 --> 01:57:28,558
Hey ! Hey !

1086
01:57:35,138 --> 01:57:39,165
Ohh. Oh, no ! Quick !
What are we gonna do ?

1087
01:57:39,242 --> 01:57:42,405
Hyah ! Hyah !

1088
01:57:42,479 --> 01:57:45,039
Tie this off.

1089
01:57:48,452 --> 01:57:51,250
- [ Gregor ] Hurry !
- Tie it !

1090
01:57:55,826 --> 01:57:58,386
- Got it !
- [ Enola ] Ah !

1091
01:58:02,299 --> 01:58:04,164
[ Screaming ]

1092
01:58:11,208 --> 01:58:13,768
Get 'em up now.

1093
01:58:20,383 --> 01:58:23,784
- [ Enola Grunting ]
- [ Gregor Laughing ]

1094
01:58:23,854 --> 01:58:27,290
- [ Gregor ] Of course !
North is south.
- What ?

1095
01:58:27,357 --> 01:58:30,724
- South is north.
- l was swimming.

1096
01:58:30,794 --> 01:58:33,024
- l saw.
- [ Gregor ] My friends.

1097
01:58:33,096 --> 01:58:35,189
My friends, look.

1098
01:58:35,265 --> 01:58:40,100
lf l take a bearing from the sun and
reverse the coordinates on Enola's back,

1099
01:58:42,139 --> 01:58:45,336
then Dryland is that way !

1100
01:59:53,210 --> 01:59:56,043
[ Sea Gull Chattering ]

1101
02:00:46,730 --> 02:00:49,756
- [ Helen Laughing ]
- lt's fresh !

1102
02:00:49,833 --> 02:00:52,495
All of this !
lt's fresh !

1103
02:00:52,569 --> 02:00:54,537
[ Helen Shrieks ]

1104
02:00:54,604 --> 02:00:59,632
[ Laughing ]

1105
02:00:59,709 --> 02:01:01,643
No !
[ Laughing ]

1106
02:01:06,182 --> 02:01:08,548
[ Helen ]
Whoo ! Whoo !

1107
02:01:08,618 --> 02:01:10,950
l found something !

1108
02:01:23,600 --> 02:01:27,195
Maybe we should put them
under the dirt.

1109
02:01:27,270 --> 02:01:29,204
l think it was their way.

1110
02:01:31,474 --> 02:01:33,442
[ Gregor ] They must have known
they were dying.

1111
02:01:33,510 --> 02:01:35,444
[ Helen Laughing ]

1112
02:01:56,299 --> 02:01:58,233
[ Winding Key ]

1113
02:02:04,074 --> 02:02:06,008
l'm home.

1114
02:02:16,920 --> 02:02:19,445
- Where's the Mariner ?
- He was outside.

1115
02:02:24,794 --> 02:02:27,456
Wait. Wait !
l want to show you this.

1116
02:02:27,530 --> 02:02:30,465
[ Birds Chirping Loudly ]

1117
02:02:42,712 --> 02:02:46,079
[ Hoofbeats ]

1118
02:02:48,752 --> 02:02:52,620
[ Whinnying ]

1119
02:03:02,065 --> 02:03:05,296
[ Birds Twittering, Chirping ]

1120
02:03:39,969 --> 02:03:42,631
First time in your life
you got nothin' to say ?

1121
02:03:57,454 --> 02:04:00,048
Enola, l have to go now.

1122
02:04:00,123 --> 02:04:02,057
But you came back for me.

1123
02:04:04,160 --> 02:04:06,094
l like you.

1124
02:04:11,234 --> 02:04:13,202
Why are you leaving ?

1125
02:04:16,005 --> 02:04:19,668
- l don't belong here.
l belong out there.
- You belong here.

1126
02:04:23,012 --> 02:04:25,879
lt's too strange here.
lt doesn't move right.

1127
02:04:25,949 --> 02:04:28,782
Helen said that
it's only land sickness.

1128
02:04:30,019 --> 02:04:33,546
We're all feeling it.
lt'll go away soon.

1129
02:04:33,623 --> 02:04:35,557
lt's more than that.

